        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 10 at 3:27AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 325 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms from Forsan to near Midkiff. Movement was east at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sterling City, Silver, Broome, Barnhart, The Intersection Of Highway
158 And Ranch Road 2059, and Us-87 Near The Coke-
Tom Green County Line.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
